'''''Star Wars: Empire's End''''' also known as '''''Dark Empire III: Empire's End''''' or simply '''''Dark Empire III''''', was a series of comics written by [[Tom Veitch]] and [[Jim Baikie]], and the end of the ''[[Star Wars: Dark Empire|Dark Empire]]'' trilogy. It was originally released by [[Dark Horse Comics]] in [[1995]] as a two-issue monthly series, then in September [[1997]] as a trade paperback.

==Publisher's summary==
''Emperor Palpatine has a new weapon&mdash;one that can annihilate a planet. But he's not targeting a planet&mdash;he's targeting the future of the Jedi, Leia's children. It looks like a hopeless situation for Luke Skywalker, who has the critical task of protecting the children. But it's not the first time Luke has found hope where none existed. The finale to the ''Dark Empire'' trilogy is collected here.''

==Opening crawl==
{{OpeningCrawl
|name=Empire's End
|text=Emperor Palpatine has deployed a terrible new weapon, once again asserting his dominance over the galaxy. With the Alliance base destroyed, and its leaders driven into hiding, many worlds sympathetic to the Alliance have capitulated to the Empire on pain of annihilation.

Luke Skywalker and his small band of Jedi have but one hope: draw the Emperor into a face-to-face confrontation, end his dark reign, and restore peace to the galaxy for all time...}}

==Plot summary==
After perishing in battle with [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke]] and [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Skywalker]] in ''Dark Empire'', [[Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] was forced to occupy an inferior clone body. Unbeknownst to him, his [[Emperor's physician|personal physician]] had been suborned by [[Carnor Jax]], backed by a number of other high-ranking Imperial personnel. The physician deliberately inserted genetic material and contaminants into all stored samples of the Emperor's original body, making these bodies far less resistant to the ravaging effects of the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] than the original.

The last remaining clone body not destroyed by Skywalker or traitorous Imperials was now aging rapidly, and Palpatine's final, irrevocable end was near unless he could either fix his genetic material (impossible since no unadulterated samples remained) or insert his spirit into another body. After consulting with ancient [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lords]] on the mausoleum planet [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]], Palpatine learned that [[Han Solo/Legends|Han]] and Leia's youngest child, [[Anakin Solo|Anakin]], was the only workable body.

In an attack on [[Byss/Legends|Byss]], the second [[Eclipse-class dreadnought|''Eclipse''-class Star Destroyer]], the ''[[Eclipse II]]'', was steered into the Galaxy Gun by [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]], and a projectile from the Gun was shot into Byss, [[Destruction of Byss|destroying it]]. Subsequently, Palpatine followed the [[Solo family/Legends|Solos]] to [[Onderon/Legends|Onderon]] and [[Battle of Onderon (Galactic Civil War)|attacked]] Leia inside the [[Kira Fortress|Kira fortress]], prompting Leia to fight back before realizing she was no match for the Emperor. Shortly after, Luke Skywalker arrived with his fellow Jedi. [[Rayf Ysanna]] was killed by a barrage of [[Force lightning/Legends|Sith lightning]], and [[Empatojayos Brand]] was mortally wounded. Skywalker, stunned that Palpatine was going for baby Anakin Solo, looked on in shock, before Sidious was shot by a [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] bolt fired by Han Solo and sadistically rushed his cackling spirit towards the infant Anakin Solo. However, he was intercepted by the body of the dying Brand, who made the ultimate sacrifice as he died, willingly clasping his soul to Palpatine's, ensuring that both of them would be pulled into the [[Netherworld of the Force/Legends|netherworld of the Force]] (in Palpatine's case, [[Chaos/Legends|Chaos]]). At long last, and with the assistance of all the Jedi of the past dragging him down, Emperor Palpatine was finally and truly killed.

